下面是一个简单的示例代码，展示了如何使用async_write函数将数据写入套接字并异步处理完成通知：

```
#include <boost/asio.hpp>
#include <iostream>

using boost::asio::ip::tcp;

void handle_write(const boost::system::error_code& error,
    std::size_t bytes_transferred)
{
    if (!error)
    {
        std::cout << "Wrote " << bytes_transferred << " bytes" << std::endl;
    }
    else
    {
        std::cerr << "Write error: " << error.message() << std::endl;
    }
}

int main()
{
    boost::asio::io_context io_context;

    tcp::socket socket(io_context);
    socket.connect({tcp::v4(), 1234});

    char data[] = "Hello, world!";
    boost::asio::async_write(socket, boost::asio::buffer(data), handle_write);

    io_context.run();

    return 0;
}
```

这个示例首先创建了一个TCP套接字，并连接到远程主机的1234端口。然后，它定义了一个包含要写入套接字的数据的缓冲区。最后，它调用async_write函数将缓冲区中的数据写入套接字，并将handle_write函数作为回调函数传递给async_write函数。在handle_write函数中，它会检查写入操作的错误码，如果没有错误则输出成功信息。最后，它通过调用io_context.run()来运行异步I/O操作，直到所有异步操作都完成为止。

不可以。调用async_write后不能立即销毁缓冲区。因为异步写入操作是非阻塞的，它会立即返回并在后台执行，而不是等待所有数据被写入并且异步操作已经完成再返回。如果在数据异步写入操作完成之前销毁缓冲区，则可能会导致写入不完整或未定义行为。

在异步写操作完成并且回调函数被调用时，缓冲区才能被销毁。因此，如果需要在异步写操作执行期间保留缓冲区数据，请确保在回调函数中处理缓冲区，直到异步操作完成。在回调函数中，可以通过读取完成的字节数并更新缓冲区指针，来处理异步写操作后剩余的数据。当异步写操作完成之后，缓冲区就可以安全删除。

以下是一个使用shared_ptr管理缓冲区的示例代码，在异步写操作完成后释放缓冲区资源：

```
#include <boost/asio.hpp>
#include <iostream>
#include <memory>

using boost::asio::ip::tcp;

void handle_write(std::shared_ptr<char> data,
    const boost::system::error_code& error,
    std::size_t bytes_transferred)
{
    if (!error)
    {
        std::cout << "Wrote " << bytes_transferred << " bytes" << std::endl;
    }
    else
    {
        std::cerr << "Write error: " << error.message() << std::endl;
    }
    // 在写操作完成后，释放缓冲区资源
    data.reset();
}

int main()
{
    boost::asio::io_context io_context;

    tcp::socket socket(io_context);
    socket.connect({tcp::v4(), 1234});

    // 使用shared_ptr管理缓冲区，以便能够在回调函数中释放资源
    std::shared_ptr<char> data = std::make_shared<char[]>(14);
    std::memcpy(data.get(), "Hello, world!", 14);
    boost::asio::async_write(socket, boost::asio::buffer(data.get(), 14),
        std::bind(handle_write, data, std::placeholders::_1, std::placeholders::_2));

    io_context.run();

    return 0;
}
```

在这个示例中，我们使用std::shared_ptr来管理缓冲区，这样可以在写操作完成后自动释放缓冲区资源。注意，在回调函数中，我们通过调用data.reset()释放shared_ptr引用计数的缓冲区的所有权。由于shared_ptr采用引用计数方式管理资源，因此只有当所有指向该资源的共享智能指针都被释放后，才会自动调用析构函数来释放资源。

使用shared_ptr可以帮助管理动态分配的缓冲区内存，确保在异步写操作之后正确释放内存，并避免内存泄漏和使用已释放的内存等问题。

Boost.Asio提供了sync_write函数用于同步写入操作，它可以将缓冲区的数据同步写入到指定套接字中。

sync_write函数的语法与async_write非常相似，但它是同步操作（阻塞式），它的调用将一直阻塞，直到所有数据被写入或发生错误。使用同步操作可能会对应用程序的性能造成一定的影响，因为它会导致当前线程被阻塞直到所有数据被写入完成。

下面是一个使用sync_write写数据的示例代码：

```c++
#include <boost/asio.hpp>
#include <iostream>

using boost::asio::ip::tcp;

int main()
{
    boost::asio::io_context io_context;

    tcp::socket socket(io_context);
    socket.connect({tcp::v4(), 1234});

    char data[] = "Hello, world!";
    boost::system::error_code error;
    std::size_t bytes_written = boost::asio::write(socket, boost::asio::buffer(data), error);
    if (!error)
    {
        std::cout << "Wrote " << bytes_written << " bytes" << std::endl;
    }
    else
    {
        std::cerr << "Write error: " << error.message() << std::endl;
    }

    return 0;
}
```

在这个示例中，它首先创建了一个TCP套接字，并连接到远程主机的1234端口。然后，它定义了一个包含要写入套接字的数据的缓冲区。最后，它调用write函数将缓冲区中的数据同步写入套接字，并检查错误码以确保数据写入成功。注意，在使用同步操作时必须谨慎地处理和处理错误，否则可能会导致应用程序崩溃或出现未定义行为。

async_receive是Boost.Asio库中用于接收异步数据的函数，它能够从指定的描述符（如套接字）异步接收数据并将其存储在指定的缓冲区中。

async_receive的参数包括：指定描述符、用于存储数据的缓冲区、接收完毕后执行的回调函数。

在调用async_receive函数时，它将立即返回，并在后台进行读取操作，当有数据到达的时候，会调用回调函数以便对接收到的数据进行处理。

以下是一个简单的使用async_receive函数来接收数据的示例代码：

```c++
#include <boost/asio.hpp>
#include <iostream>

using boost::asio::ip::tcp;

void handle_receive(const boost::system::error_code& error,
    std::size_t bytes_transferred)
{
    if (!error)
    {
        std::cout << "Received " << bytes_transferred << " bytes" << std::endl;
    }
    else
    {
        std::cerr << "Receive error: " << error.message() << std::endl;
    }
}

int main()
{
    boost::asio::io_context io_context;

    tcp::socket socket(io_context);
    socket.connect({tcp::v4(), 1234});

    char buffer[1024];
    boost::asio::async_read(socket, boost::asio::buffer(buffer), handle_receive);

    io_context.run();

    return 0;
}
```

在这个示例中，它首先创建了一个TCP套接字，并连接到远程主机的1234端口。然后，它定义了一个用于存储接收数据的缓冲区。最后，它调用async_receive函数异步读取指定的套接字并将数据存储到缓冲区中，同时将handle_receive函数作为回调函数传递给async_receive函数。在handle_receive函数中，它检查读取操作的错误码并输出接收到的字节数。最后，它通过调用io_context.run()来运行异步I/O操作，直到所有异步操作都完成为止。

pthread_attr_setschedpolicy and sched_setscheduler are two different functions used in Linux for setting the scheduling policy of threads. The main difference between them is that pthread_attr_setschedpolicy is used to set the scheduling policy for a thread attribute object, while sched_setscheduler is used to set the scheduling policy for a running thread.

pthread_attr_setschedpolicy:
pthread_attr_setschedpolicy is a function that sets the scheduling policy attribute value of the thread attribute object referenced by the attr parameter. This attribute value will be used by the pthread_create function when a new thread is created. The scheduling policy determines how the operating system schedules a thread to run on the CPU.

sched_setscheduler:
sched_setscheduler is a function that sets the scheduling policy and scheduling parameters for a running thread. The parameters are specified in the sched_param structure. The scheduling policy and parameters determine how the operating system schedules the thread to run on the CPU.

Example:

```c
#include <pthread.h>
#include <sched.h>

void *thread_func(void *arg) {
    // thread code
}

int main() {
    pthread_t thread;
    pthread_attr_t attr; 

    // Create thread attribute object
    pthread_attr_init(&attr);

    // Set scheduling policy for attribute object
    pthread_attr_setschedpolicy(&attr, SCHED_FIFO);

    // Create thread with attribute
    pthread_create(&thread, &attr, thread_func, NULL);

    // Set scheduling policy for running thread
    struct sched_param param;
    param.sched_priority = 1;
    sched_setscheduler(thread, SCHED_FIFO, &param);

    // Wait for thread to finish
    pthread_join(thread, NULL);

    return 0;
}
```

In the above example, we first create a thread attribute object and set its scheduling policy using pthread_attr_setschedpolicy. Then we create a new thread using this attribute object. Later, we set the scheduling policy and parameters for the running thread using sched_setscheduler. Finally, we wait for the thread to finish using pthread_join. This example shows how to use both functions to set the scheduling policy for a thread.

The main difference between the two functions `pthread_attr_setschedpolicy()` and `sched_setscheduler()` is that the first is used for setting the scheduling policy for a new pthread, whereas the second one is used for setting the scheduling policy for an existing thread or process.

Here's a simple illustration of both the functions in the same C program:

```c
#include <pthread.h>
#include <sched.h>
#include <stdio.h>
#include <unistd.h>

void *thread_function(void *arg) {
  printf("Thread started\n");
  sleep(1);
  printf("Thread end\n");
  return NULL;
}

int main() {
  pthread_t thread;
  pthread_attr_t attr;
  struct sched_param param;

  // Set the scheduling policy and priority for the newly created pthread
  pthread_attr_init(&attr);
  pthread_attr_setschedpolicy(&attr, SCHED_FIFO);
  param.sched_priority = 10;
  pthread_attr_setschedparam(&attr, &param);

  // Create the pthread with the specified SCHED_FIFO policy and priority 10
  if (pthread_create(&thread, &attr, thread_function, NULL) != 0) {
    perror("pthread_create");
    return 1;
  }

  // Set the scheduling policy and priority for the main thread or process
  param.sched_priority = 20;
  if (sched_setscheduler(getpid(), SCHED_RR, &param) != 0) {
    perror("sched_setscheduler");
    return 1;
  }

  printf("Main started\n");
  // Now join the pthread
  pthread_join(thread, NULL);
  printf("Main end\n");
  return 0;
}
```

In this C program, we're setting up a new pthread_attr_t object and using that attr object with the `pthread_create()` function to create a separately scheduled thread. We use `pthread_attr_setschedpolicy()` to set the scheduling policy for the new thread.

For the main thread (the process itself), we use `sched_setscheduler()` to set the scheduling policy and priority directly. Note that the main thread will continue with the default scheduling policy and priority if we don't change it with `sched_setscheduler()`. The `getpid()` function is used to get the process ID (or thread ID, in the case of the main thread).

In the C program below, a thread is created, and you can change the priority of the thread using command line arguments.

```c
#include <pthread.h>
#include <sched.h>
#include <stdio.h>
#include <stdlib.h>
#include <unistd.h>

void *thread_function(void *arg) {
  printf("Thread started\n");
  sleep(1);
  printf("Thread end\n");
  return NULL;
}

int main(int argc, char *argv[]) {
  pthread_t thread;
  pthread_attr_t attr;
  struct sched_param param;

  if (argc < 2) {
    printf("Usage: %s <priority>\n", argv[0]);
    return 1;
  }

  int priority = atoi(argv[1]);

  // Set the scheduling policy and priority for the newly created pthread
  pthread_attr_init(&attr);
  pthread_attr_setschedpolicy(&attr, SCHED_FIFO);
  param.sched_priority = priority;
  pthread_attr_setschedparam(&attr, &param);

  // Create the pthread with the specified SCHED_FIFO policy and priority
  if (pthread_create(&thread, &attr, thread_function, NULL) != 0) {
    perror("pthread_create");
    return 1;
  }

  printf("Main started\n");
  // Now join the pthread
  pthread_join(thread, NULL);
  printf("Main end\n");
  return 0;
}
```

To compile and run the program:

1. Save the above code to a file named `change_thread_priority.c`.
2. Open a terminal and navigate to the file's location.
3. Compile the program using: `gcc change_thread_priority.c -o change_thread_priority -lpthread`
4. Run the program with a priority of your choice: `./change_thread_priority 10`

Please note that on some systems, you may need to run the program with root privileges in order to set realtime scheduling policies (SCHED_FIFO or SCHED_RR) and high priorities. In this case, you can run the program using `sudo`:

```sh
sudo ./change_thread_priority 10
```

```c
#include <stdio.h>
#include <stdlib.h>
#include <signal.h>
#include <unistd.h>
#include <stdbool.h>

static bool regular_signal_handled = false;
static bool rt_signal_handled = false;

void signal_handler(int signum)
{
    if (signum == SIGUSR1)
    {
        printf("Обработка обычного сигнала...\n");
        regular_signal_handled = true;
    }
    else if (signum == SIGRTMIN)
    {
        printf("Обработка сигнала реального времени...\n");
        rt_signal_handled = true;
    }
}

int main(void)
{
    struct sigaction regular_signal;
    struct sigaction rt_signal;

    regular_signal.sa_handler = signal_handler;
    sigemptyset(&regular_signal.sa_mask);
    regular_signal.sa_flags = 0;

    rt_signal.sa_handler = signal_handler;
    sigemptyset(&rt_signal.sa_mask);
    rt_signal.sa_flags = 0;

    if (sigaction(SIGUSR1, &regular_signal, NULL) == -1 ||
        sigaction(SIGRTMIN, &rt_signal, NULL) == -1)
    {
        perror("sigaction");
        exit(EXIT_FAILURE);
    }

    sleep(5);

    kill(getpid(), SIGUSR1);
    kill(getpid(), SIGRTMIN);

    while (!regular_signal_handled || !rt_signal_handled)
    {
        if (!regular_signal_handled)
        {
            printf("Ожидание обычного сигнала...\n");
        }
        if (!rt_signal_handled)
        {
            printf("Ожидание сигнала реального времени...\n");
        }
        sleep(1);
    }

    printf("Очередь для различных типов сигналов успешно организована!\n");
    return EXIT_SUCCESS;
}
```

В данной программе мы определяем два обработчика сигналов - один для обычного сигнала (SIGUSR1) и один для сигнала реального времени (SIGRTMIN). Затем мы ждем, когда обработчики сигналов сработают и устанавливают соответствующие значения переменных-флагов.

На каждом шаге цикла while мы проверяем, обработаны ли оба сигнала, и ожидаем их, если нет. Если оба флага становятся равными `true` (а значит, отработала очередь для двух типов сигналов), мы выводим сообщение об успешной организации очереди.

Ниже приведена программа на языке Си, которая демонстрирует приоритеты сигналов реального времени по сравнению с обычными сигналами:

```c
#include <stdio.h>
#include <stdlib.h>
#include <signal.h>
#include <unistd.h>

void signal_handler(int signum)
{
    if (signum == SIGUSR1)
    {
        printf("Обработка обычного сигнала SIGUSR1...\n");
    }
    else if (signum == SIGRTMIN)
    {
        printf("Обработка сигнала реального времени SIGRTMIN...\n");
    }
}

int main(void)
{
    struct sigaction regular_signal;
    struct sigaction rt_signal;

    regular_signal.sa_handler = signal_handler;
    sigemptyset(&regular_signal.sa_mask);
    regular_signal.sa_flags = 0;

    rt_signal.sa_handler = signal_handler;
    sigemptyset(&rt_signal.sa_mask);
    rt_signal.sa_flags = 0;

    if (sigaction(SIGUSR1, &regular_signal, NULL) == -1 ||
        sigaction(SIGRTMIN, &rt_signal, NULL) == -1)
    {
        perror("sigaction");
        exit(EXIT_FAILURE);
    }

    printf("Отправление обычного сигнала SIGUSR1...\n");
    kill(getpid(), SIGUSR1);

    printf("Отправление сигнала реального времени SIGRTMIN...\n");
    kill(getpid(), SIGRTMIN);

    sleep(5);  // Даем время обработчикам сигналов выполнить свою работу
    printf("Завершение программы.\n");
    return EXIT_SUCCESS;
}
```

На этот раз, мы отправляем сигналы в определенном порядке: сначала обычный (SIGUSR1), а затем сигнал реального времени (SIGRTMIN). Вы можете заметить, что в выводе программы обработка сигнала реального времени происходит до обычного сигнала, вне зависимости от порядка отправки.

```plaintext
Отправление обычного сигнала SIGUSR1...
Отправление сигнала реального времени SIGRTMIN...
Обработка сигнала реального времени SIGRTMIN...
Обработка обычного сигнала SIGUSR1...
Завершение программы.
```

Таким образом, опытным путем было подтверждено наличие приоритетов сигналов реального времени по отношению к обычным сигналам в программе на языке Си.

