The singularities of the Euler angle rotations are the values of $\theta$ where the tangent of $\theta$ becomes undefined. These values are $0$, $\pi$, and $\pm\frac{\pi}{2}$, depending on the sequence. When $\theta$ approaches these values, the rotations become ill-defined or degenerate, and the coordinate system loses a degree of freedom. These singularities can cause problems in certain applications, such as robotics and aerospace engineering.

